WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:17.490 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.490 --> 00:00:20.000 align:middle line:10%
Hi, I'm Lisa Garr, host
of Gaiam Inspirations.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.850 align:middle line:10%
Welcome to our beautiful
Los Angeles studio.

00:00:22.850 --> 00:00:26.410 align:middle line:10%
In 1997, "The Four Agreements"
was written by Toltec Shaman,

00:00:26.410 --> 00:00:28.890 align:middle line:10%
Don Miguel Ruiz, and spent
seven years on the New

00:00:28.890 --> 00:00:30.810 align:middle line:10%
York Times bestseller list.

00:00:30.810 --> 00:00:33.760 align:middle line:84%
And today, I'm very honored
to be joined by Don Miguel

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:37.320 align:middle line:84%
Ruiz and his son,
Don Miguel Ruiz, Jr.,

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:40.920 align:middle line:84%
to share the wisdom of the
centuries-old Toltec tradition

00:00:40.920 --> 00:00:45.110 align:middle line:84%
that serves as a guide to an
individual's personal freedom.

00:00:45.110 --> 00:00:47.670 align:middle line:10%
Don Miguel Jr. actually
has a new book out called,

00:00:47.670 --> 00:00:51.930 align:middle line:10%
"The Five Levels of Attachment
: Toltec Wisdom for the Modern

00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:55.350 align:middle line:10%
World", which explores the
concept of how our attachments

00:00:55.350 --> 00:00:57.230 align:middle line:10%
have created our reality.

00:00:57.230 --> 00:00:58.410 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:00:58.410 --> 00:01:00.550 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much, both
of you, for being here.

00:01:00.550 --> 00:01:01.677 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for having us.

00:01:01.677 --> 00:01:02.410 align:middle line:90%
This is a great honor.

00:01:02.410 --> 00:01:03.730 align:middle line:90%
Oh, the honor is mine.

00:01:03.730 --> 00:01:06.050 align:middle line:84%
It's a big pressure to
be on this with your show.

00:01:06.050 --> 00:01:08.060 align:middle line:84%
Well I love learning
from you, and I've

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:10.160 align:middle line:90%
enjoyed your book so much.

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:11.600 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to start
with you, actually,

00:01:11.600 --> 00:01:15.050 align:middle line:84%
Don Miguel Sr. When you were
raised, where were you raised?

00:01:15.050 --> 00:01:16.180 align:middle line:90%
In what area?

00:01:16.180 --> 00:01:19.510 align:middle line:10%
Well I grew up in Tijuana.

00:01:19.510 --> 00:01:24.340 align:middle line:10%
Even that-- I was born in
Guadalajara, but legally

00:01:24.340 --> 00:01:26.680 align:middle line:10%
I am from Tijuana.

00:01:26.680 --> 00:01:30.900 align:middle line:84%
Then I was raised until
I was 13, 14 years old.

00:01:30.900 --> 00:01:36.460 align:middle line:84%
And then we moved to Mexico City
where my brothers were studying

00:01:36.460 --> 00:01:39.230 align:middle line:90%
for-- to be medical doctors.

00:01:39.230 --> 00:01:43.420 align:middle line:84%
And later on, I also
became a medical doctor,

00:01:43.420 --> 00:01:45.540 align:middle line:90%
just following their guide.

00:01:45.540 --> 00:01:49.590 align:middle line:84%
You've-- I heard you refer
to yourself once as Dr.

00:01:49.590 --> 00:01:53.840 align:middle line:84%
Ruiz and you were a
neurosurgeon, or--

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:55.405 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:01:55.405 --> 00:01:57.260 align:middle line:90%
How many years?

00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:01.370 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's-- it's hard
to really remember.

00:02:01.370 --> 00:02:04.310 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I practice to
surgery with my brothers

00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:07.620 align:middle line:84%
like for four or five years,
maybe then six years .

00:02:07.620 --> 00:02:09.620 align:middle line:84%
And one of my brothers
is a neurosurgeon,

00:02:09.620 --> 00:02:12.520 align:middle line:84%
and the other is an
oncologist associate.

00:02:12.520 --> 00:02:15.057 align:middle line:84%
Then I was part of
their team, which

00:02:15.057 --> 00:02:16.390 align:middle line:84%
means that I did a
lot of neurosurgeries

00:02:16.390 --> 00:02:19.220 align:middle line:90%
with my brother, Carlos.

00:02:19.220 --> 00:02:20.610 align:middle line:90%
I did not know that about you.

00:02:20.610 --> 00:02:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And when you were
raised, you were raised

00:02:23.300 --> 00:02:24.520 align:middle line:90%
with the Toltec tradition.

00:02:24.520 --> 00:02:27.670 align:middle line:84%
In some ways, I think the
modern family has lost a lot

00:02:27.670 --> 00:02:29.590 align:middle line:90%
of tradition, here in the US.

00:02:29.590 --> 00:02:36.110 align:middle line:84%
What ways did you remember
as meaningful in your life,

00:02:36.110 --> 00:02:37.980 align:middle line:90%
when you were raised?

00:02:37.980 --> 00:02:41.190 align:middle line:84%
Well mainly, it's
about respect.

00:02:41.190 --> 00:02:44.530 align:middle line:84%
I see how my parents treat each
other with a lot of respect.

00:02:44.530 --> 00:02:47.200 align:middle line:84%
How they treat the children
with a lot of respect.

00:02:47.200 --> 00:02:49.780 align:middle line:84%
And also how they treat
the rest of their relatives

00:02:49.780 --> 00:02:52.330 align:middle line:84%
and their friends
with a lot of respect.

00:02:52.330 --> 00:02:55.590 align:middle line:84%
And of course everybody
respects them, like everybody

00:02:55.590 --> 00:02:58.810 align:middle line:90%
call my father Don Ruiz.

00:02:58.810 --> 00:03:00.690 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of
respect for my father

00:03:00.690 --> 00:03:02.170 align:middle line:90%
that people-- that people have.

00:03:02.170 --> 00:03:03.130 align:middle line:90%
That is-- I love.

00:03:03.130 --> 00:03:05.460 align:middle line:84%
And now how did you
transfer that on when

00:03:05.460 --> 00:03:07.470 align:middle line:90%
you're raising your children?

00:03:07.470 --> 00:03:09.500 align:middle line:84%
Your son, and you
have-- we actually have

00:03:09.500 --> 00:03:12.380 align:middle line:90%
a picture of your two sons.

00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:14.790 align:middle line:84%
There's actually three
sons that you have,

00:03:14.790 --> 00:03:16.965 align:middle line:90%
Don Miguel, Don Jose--

00:03:16.965 --> 00:03:17.990 align:middle line:90%
And Leo.

00:03:17.990 --> 00:03:19.080 align:middle line:90%
And Leo.

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:21.240 align:middle line:84%
And how did you
raise your children?

00:03:21.240 --> 00:03:25.585 align:middle line:84%
Well, we never planned
how to raise the children.

00:03:25.585 --> 00:03:26.630 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:03:26.630 --> 00:03:31.140 align:middle line:84%
When I have my-- my first child,
I had no experience at all.

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:33.450 align:middle line:90%
Then it's about the action.

00:03:33.450 --> 00:03:37.300 align:middle line:84%
It's-- it's about
how we love them.

00:03:37.300 --> 00:03:43.280 align:middle line:84%
I remember having Miguel in my
hands when finally he was born.

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:46.080 align:middle line:84%
And I take him out,
there was a full moon,

00:03:46.080 --> 00:03:47.630 align:middle line:90%
and I offered him to the moon.

00:03:47.630 --> 00:03:50.510 align:middle line:90%
I say, he's alive.

00:03:50.510 --> 00:03:57.820 align:middle line:84%
And he will go around the
world, sharing himself.

00:03:57.820 --> 00:03:59.910 align:middle line:84%
And have you raised--
now you have two

00:03:59.910 --> 00:04:01.719 align:middle line:84%
children as well, don't you?
-Yes.

00:04:01.719 --> 00:04:03.720 align:middle line:84%
I have my son, Alejandro,
and my little girl, Audrey.

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:05.650 align:middle line:90%
They're both seven and five.

00:04:05.650 --> 00:04:06.480 align:middle line:90%
And it's nice.

00:04:06.480 --> 00:04:08.900 align:middle line:84%
You know, like that story
that my father was telling me.

00:04:08.900 --> 00:04:12.230 align:middle line:84%
Like when I held my son
for the very first time,

00:04:12.230 --> 00:04:15.360 align:middle line:90%
a huge realization came upon me.

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:17.560 align:middle line:90%
I have no idea what I'm doing.

00:04:17.560 --> 00:04:18.380 align:middle line:90%
No idea.

00:04:18.380 --> 00:04:19.779 align:middle line:84%
And then, all of a
sudden, it dawned on me

00:04:19.779 --> 00:04:22.100 align:middle line:84%
that he has no idea what
he has been doing for,

00:04:22.100 --> 00:04:23.940 align:middle line:90%
what, at the time, 30 years?

00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:25.420 align:middle line:90%
We would play it by ear.

00:04:25.420 --> 00:04:29.790 align:middle line:84%
The thing about raising a child
is that we grab from what we

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:33.190 align:middle line:84%
know, from our family, from
our friends, from everyone's

00:04:33.190 --> 00:04:34.640 align:middle line:90%
giving us advice.

00:04:34.640 --> 00:04:36.470 align:middle line:90%
And we use what we apply.

00:04:36.470 --> 00:04:40.000 align:middle line:84%
The question is, do we impose
an image onto our kids?

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:43.630 align:middle line:84%
Or do I engage my
child, and my child

00:04:43.630 --> 00:04:46.730 align:middle line:90%
tells me what he or she needs?

00:04:46.730 --> 00:04:50.250 align:middle line:84%
And, to me, that's how I've
really learned from my dad,

00:04:50.250 --> 00:04:53.830 align:middle line:84%
how to raise my kids
in-- for who they are.

00:04:53.830 --> 00:04:55.900 align:middle line:84%
It starts with
accepting who they are,

00:04:55.900 --> 00:04:58.750 align:middle line:84%
to love them for who
they are, and raise

00:04:58.750 --> 00:05:01.410 align:middle line:84%
them as they-- as they are.
-As they are.

00:05:01.410 --> 00:05:03.790 align:middle line:84%
Now did you-- have
a lot of you--

00:05:03.790 --> 00:05:05.520 align:middle line:84%
you are so wonderful
to share so many family

00:05:05.520 --> 00:05:07.830 align:middle line:84%
photos with us, which I
really, really appreciate.

00:05:07.830 --> 00:05:10.550 align:middle line:84%
Because we get a
glimpse into your lives.

00:05:10.550 --> 00:05:13.720 align:middle line:84%
Did you used to take your sons
on a lot of journeys together?

00:05:13.720 --> 00:05:14.920 align:middle line:90%
We have a picture here of you.

00:05:14.920 --> 00:05:16.511 align:middle line:84%
I think you were
in a-- in a cave.

00:05:16.511 --> 00:05:17.210 align:middle line:90%
Definitely.

00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:19.440 align:middle line:84%
I just come in my
memory something

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:22.060 align:middle line:90%
that I really like a lot.

00:05:22.060 --> 00:05:26.860 align:middle line:84%
The first time that I have his
son, Alejandro, in my hands,

00:05:26.860 --> 00:05:31.470 align:middle line:84%
and I say, wow, he is--
he is so beautiful.

00:05:31.470 --> 00:05:33.640 align:middle line:84%
Then I put him in his
hand and say, now--

00:05:33.640 --> 00:05:34.760 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:36.380 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:05:36.380 --> 00:05:37.080 align:middle line:90%
You remember that.

00:05:37.080 --> 00:05:39.540 align:middle line:84%
What do you mean,
domesticate him?

00:05:39.540 --> 00:05:42.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, when my dad taught me
that-- because in "The Four

00:05:42.590 --> 00:05:45.300 align:middle line:84%
Agreements", he talks about
letting go of domestication.

00:05:45.300 --> 00:05:47.850 align:middle line:84%
And then he went to
me and says, Miguel,

00:05:47.850 --> 00:05:49.860 align:middle line:90%
domesticated your child.

00:05:49.860 --> 00:05:51.310 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why
he told me that

00:05:51.310 --> 00:05:54.190 align:middle line:84%
is because, if I'm not going
to domesticate my child,

00:05:54.190 --> 00:05:54.920 align:middle line:90%
someone else will.

00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:55.620 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:05:55.620 --> 00:05:58.130 align:middle line:90%
But the question is, how?

00:05:58.130 --> 00:06:01.380 align:middle line:84%
Life teaches us, or domesticates
us in its own way, which

00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:03.190 align:middle line:90%
is called action-reaction.

00:06:03.190 --> 00:06:05.042 align:middle line:84%
For every action
we take, there is

00:06:05.042 --> 00:06:07.070 align:middle line:90%
a consequence, and a reaction.

00:06:07.070 --> 00:06:09.930 align:middle line:84%
This is how life teaches
us from our mistakes,

00:06:09.930 --> 00:06:12.310 align:middle line:90%
from our-- how we learn.

00:06:12.310 --> 00:06:14.020 align:middle line:90%
And we build from that.

00:06:14.020 --> 00:06:16.030 align:middle line:84%
Whereas, the domestication
my father talks

00:06:16.030 --> 00:06:18.480 align:middle line:84%
about in "The Four
Agreements", and throughout,

00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:20.350 align:middle line:90%
is based on conditional love.

00:06:20.350 --> 00:06:24.820 align:middle line:84%
A system of reward and
punishment for everything--

00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:29.430 align:middle line:84%
if we do something right, the
reward is our own acceptance.

00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:32.420 align:middle line:84%
If we do something wrong,
the punishment is rejection.

00:06:32.420 --> 00:06:35.780 align:middle line:84%
Since we're emotional
beings, that acceptance

00:06:35.780 --> 00:06:37.250 align:middle line:90%
feels like love.

00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:40.570 align:middle line:84%
If we do it wrong,
that rejection

00:06:40.570 --> 00:06:42.080 align:middle line:90%
feels like the opposite.

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:44.070 align:middle line:84%
So we're talking
about domestication

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:45.860 align:middle line:90%
through conditional love.

00:06:45.860 --> 00:06:48.800 align:middle line:84%
So when my father's telling
me, domesticate your child,

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:53.150 align:middle line:84%
he's telling me, engage and
teach them how to live in life.

00:06:53.150 --> 00:06:56.530 align:middle line:84%
Do it in your own way,
but always become aware

00:06:56.530 --> 00:07:01.710 align:middle line:84%
that how I do it, do I do
it with conditional love,

00:07:01.710 --> 00:07:05.550 align:middle line:84%
or unconditional, which is
accepting him for who he is.

00:07:05.550 --> 00:07:08.270 align:middle line:84%
So still allow him to
make his own mistakes,

00:07:08.270 --> 00:07:09.770 align:middle line:84%
fall on his knees,
do whatever he

00:07:09.770 --> 00:07:14.370 align:middle line:84%
needs to do to learn self-love,
but yet, be there as a support.

00:07:14.370 --> 00:07:15.070 align:middle line:90%
Yeah because--

00:07:15.070 --> 00:07:16.529 align:middle line:84%
-Not do it for him.
-Exactly.

00:07:16.529 --> 00:07:19.430 align:middle line:84%
Because the world around him--
and I know this for a fact,

00:07:19.430 --> 00:07:23.950 align:middle line:84%
because I had him as a father--
but I still was domesticated.

00:07:23.950 --> 00:07:27.790 align:middle line:84%
I still fell into conditional
love through my friends,

00:07:27.790 --> 00:07:30.300 align:middle line:84%
through our school,
through pop culture,

00:07:30.300 --> 00:07:32.710 align:middle line:84%
through my-- you know,
like I-- I remember

00:07:32.710 --> 00:07:35.690 align:middle line:90%
my rebellion with my family.

00:07:35.690 --> 00:07:38.455 align:middle line:84%
Having the juxtaposition
of love between my father,

00:07:38.455 --> 00:07:41.800 align:middle line:84%
and my grandmother, my
mother, and my cousins,

00:07:41.800 --> 00:07:44.670 align:middle line:84%
and then having the conditional
acceptance of friends.

00:07:44.670 --> 00:07:47.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, and with our
friends in high school--

00:07:47.510 --> 00:07:49.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to use an
example of junior high

00:07:49.020 --> 00:07:51.940 align:middle line:84%
because the reward for
living up the expectation

00:07:51.940 --> 00:07:54.040 align:middle line:90%
is popularity, acceptance.

00:07:54.040 --> 00:07:54.980 align:middle line:90%
Cool.

00:07:54.980 --> 00:07:59.270 align:middle line:84%
If you do not, then you're
a square, you're a nerd,

00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:01.720 align:middle line:84%
you're a geek, and
you're chastised.

00:08:01.720 --> 00:08:05.730 align:middle line:84%
So basically, without
separation, the world

00:08:05.730 --> 00:08:08.970 align:middle line:84%
out there is ready to
domesticate us according

00:08:08.970 --> 00:08:11.330 align:middle line:90%
to its own conditions.

00:08:11.330 --> 00:08:14.480 align:middle line:84%
And the question
is, are-- is there

00:08:14.480 --> 00:08:17.220 align:middle line:90%
going to be a counterbalance?

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:20.090 align:middle line:84%
So for me, my father's and
my grandmother's teaching

00:08:20.090 --> 00:08:22.540 align:middle line:90%
was that counterbalance.

00:08:22.540 --> 00:08:24.800 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
being the eldest,

00:08:24.800 --> 00:08:27.390 align:middle line:84%
I also got to witness my
own father's transformation.

00:08:27.390 --> 00:08:30.870 align:middle line:84%
I remember the man before
he started his journey.

00:08:30.870 --> 00:08:33.890 align:middle line:84%
I remember the man
who was still doctor.

00:08:33.890 --> 00:08:36.530 align:middle line:84%
And I remember as
a six-year-old,

00:08:36.530 --> 00:08:39.620 align:middle line:84%
and a seven-year-old, and
an eight-year-old, that guy.

00:08:39.620 --> 00:08:42.049 align:middle line:90%
Then he began his journey.

00:08:42.049 --> 00:08:45.200 align:middle line:84%
I remember the day when he
let go of medicine, my mom's

00:08:45.200 --> 00:08:48.500 align:middle line:84%
reaction, my grandma's
reaction, everyone's reaction,

00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:50.890 align:middle line:84%
and-- and you're
going to go do what?

00:08:50.890 --> 00:08:51.590 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:08:51.590 --> 00:08:53.391 align:middle line:84%
So did it register
to you as fear?

00:08:53.391 --> 00:08:54.090 align:middle line:90%
Change?

00:08:54.090 --> 00:08:55.950 align:middle line:84%
Well, for me, yes,
because it was everything--

00:08:55.950 --> 00:08:58.190 align:middle line:90%
the whole world shifted for us.

00:08:58.190 --> 00:09:03.020 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, at
a-- watching his transition,

00:09:03.020 --> 00:09:06.180 align:middle line:84%
watching his movement,
all of a sudden

00:09:06.180 --> 00:09:08.560 align:middle line:84%
allowed me to witness
something incredible,

00:09:08.560 --> 00:09:12.150 align:middle line:84%
which is the blossoming of this
man, right here, right now.

00:09:12.150 --> 00:09:14.770 align:middle line:84%
So for me, having that
combination of how

00:09:14.770 --> 00:09:17.330 align:middle line:84%
my dad domesticated
me in my own life,

00:09:17.330 --> 00:09:19.400 align:middle line:84%
going from conditional
domestication

00:09:19.400 --> 00:09:21.000 align:middle line:84%
when I was a kid,
like eight-years-old,

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:23.580 align:middle line:84%
seven-years-old,
then watching him,

00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:26.780 align:middle line:84%
throughout my
teenage years, shift.

00:09:26.780 --> 00:09:30.380 align:middle line:84%
And then watching him, because
I was already in my late teens

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:34.600 align:middle line:84%
or 20s when he became a
master, and how he domesticated

00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:37.930 align:middle line:84%
and educated my younger
brother, in particular, Leo,

00:09:37.930 --> 00:09:40.550 align:middle line:90%
how that bridge was different.

00:09:40.550 --> 00:09:43.830 align:middle line:84%
And watching that for
myself, especially as I'm

00:09:43.830 --> 00:09:46.890 align:middle line:84%
raising my own kid, allows
me the juxtaposition

00:09:46.890 --> 00:09:49.140 align:middle line:90%
of those two things.

00:09:49.140 --> 00:09:50.900 align:middle line:84%
Now when you went
through that time

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:52.440 align:middle line:90%
and that period of rebellion.

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:55.320 align:middle line:84%
Was that your journey,
in order to see

00:09:55.320 --> 00:09:58.230 align:middle line:84%
what was-- what the difference
was out there, in the world?

