I have to live up
to what I know.

00:20:26.560 --> 00:20:29.390 align:middle line:84%
Like you had done
when you were a child.

00:20:29.390 --> 00:20:30.270 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:20:30.270 --> 00:20:32.870 align:middle line:90%
Level Five, Fanaticism.

00:20:32.870 --> 00:20:37.210 align:middle line:84%
I'm so attached to knowledge
that knowledge controls my

00:20:37.210 --> 00:20:40.240 align:middle line:90%
every action, without a doubt.

00:20:40.240 --> 00:20:45.270 align:middle line:84%
It's the distortion of
knowledge, because now,

00:20:45.270 --> 00:20:50.950 align:middle line:84%
where knowledge no longer
reflects life as is.

00:20:50.950 --> 00:20:52.060 align:middle line:84%
Because the function
of knowledge

00:20:52.060 --> 00:20:54.170 align:middle line:84%
is for us to
understand the world,

00:20:54.170 --> 00:20:56.430 align:middle line:90%
to understand each other.

00:20:56.430 --> 00:20:58.490 align:middle line:84%
But when I'm so
attached to knowledge,

00:20:58.490 --> 00:21:02.990 align:middle line:84%
my personal importance, my
ego, will distort what I see,

00:21:02.990 --> 00:21:07.400 align:middle line:84%
and I can force it to fit
what I want it to see,

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:09.220 align:middle line:90%
and reject anything else.

00:21:09.220 --> 00:21:12.050 align:middle line:84%
It's the rigidness, you
can say, to the point

00:21:12.050 --> 00:21:15.510 align:middle line:84%
where, an idea is more
important than my own life.

00:21:15.510 --> 00:21:17.881 align:middle line:84%
You talked about that a little
bit in "The Four Agreements",

00:21:17.881 --> 00:21:18.580 align:middle line:90%
didn't you?

00:21:18.580 --> 00:21:22.730 align:middle line:84%
About the attachment
to-- to knowledge,

00:21:22.730 --> 00:21:29.440 align:middle line:84%
but it was described as-- as
don't take anything personally.

00:21:29.440 --> 00:21:32.460 align:middle line:90%
Is that where it was described?

00:21:32.460 --> 00:21:34.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, when I say,
don't make assumptions--

00:21:34.430 --> 00:21:35.230 align:middle line:90%
Don't make assumptions.

00:21:35.230 --> 00:21:35.950 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:21:35.950 --> 00:21:38.730 align:middle line:84%
 --even deeper into
what knowledge is,

00:21:38.730 --> 00:21:44.290 align:middle line:84%
and what I say is that, when we
were born, we had no knowledge.

00:21:44.290 --> 00:21:48.300 align:middle line:84%
We create knowledge, and then
when we give our personal power

00:21:48.300 --> 00:21:50.250 align:middle line:84%
to knowledge, and
knowledge becomes

00:21:50.250 --> 00:21:53.730 align:middle line:90%
the biggest tyrant in our life.

00:21:53.730 --> 00:21:58.370 align:middle line:84%
And knowledge
creates our identity.

00:21:58.370 --> 00:22:00.260 align:middle line:90%
What we believe we are.

00:22:00.260 --> 00:22:05.040 align:middle line:84%
So do you live
without knowledge, now?

00:22:05.040 --> 00:22:06.290 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:22:06.290 --> 00:22:09.750 align:middle line:90%
I use knowledge.

00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:11.890 align:middle line:90%
Otherwise I cannot speak to you.

00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:12.870 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:22:12.870 --> 00:22:18.720 align:middle line:84%
Then knowledge follows
whatever duration I want to go.

00:22:18.720 --> 00:22:20.960 align:middle line:84%
But you're detached from
it, at the same time, right?

00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:21.660 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:22:21.660 --> 00:22:24.370 align:middle line:84%
 --the things,
like could say that

00:22:24.370 --> 00:22:28.910 align:middle line:84%
there's a separation between
me, life, and knowledge.

00:22:28.910 --> 00:22:30.900 align:middle line:90%
Because what is knowledge?

00:22:30.900 --> 00:22:33.900 align:middle line:84%
Knowledge is a
symbol that allows

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:36.230 align:middle line:90%
us to understand the world.

00:22:36.230 --> 00:22:39.740 align:middle line:84%
You can say that it
allows us to comprehend

00:22:39.740 --> 00:22:41.470 align:middle line:90%
how the universe works.

00:22:41.470 --> 00:22:45.510 align:middle line:84%
It allows us to
comprehend each other,

00:22:45.510 --> 00:22:49.470 align:middle line:84%
and through that we make the
agreements by which we create

00:22:49.470 --> 00:22:51.030 align:middle line:90%
this society, this culture.

00:22:51.030 --> 00:22:53.790 align:middle line:84%
Everything around this
city, in Los Angeles,

00:22:53.790 --> 00:22:57.670 align:middle line:90%
was created by a yes and a no.

00:22:57.670 --> 00:22:59.600 align:middle line:84%
But the thing about
knowledge is that it's

00:22:59.600 --> 00:23:02.390 align:middle line:90%
subjugate to an agreement.

00:23:02.390 --> 00:23:05.100 align:middle line:84%
You can say even a
word, its definition

00:23:05.100 --> 00:23:08.470 align:middle line:84%
is completely subjugate
to a community's agreement

00:23:08.470 --> 00:23:10.200 align:middle line:90%
of what that word means.

00:23:10.200 --> 00:23:14.280 align:middle line:84%
So in essence, everything we
know, every single concept,

00:23:14.280 --> 00:23:17.090 align:middle line:84%
is an expression of
the agreements of us,

00:23:17.090 --> 00:23:20.260 align:middle line:84%
as the dreams-- as human
beings coming together,

00:23:20.260 --> 00:23:24.120 align:middle line:84%
saying this is what
this word means.

00:23:24.120 --> 00:23:27.760 align:middle line:84%
I can say, this is a
sofa, this is a shirt,

00:23:27.760 --> 00:23:30.980 align:middle line:84%
and there's things that
aren't tangible like that.

00:23:30.980 --> 00:23:33.370 align:middle line:90%
There's love, there's justice.

00:23:33.370 --> 00:23:37.970 align:middle line:84%
So its definition is how we
allow ourselves to comprehend.

00:23:37.970 --> 00:23:43.120 align:middle line:84%
Now when you have
something that changeable,

00:23:43.120 --> 00:23:48.210 align:middle line:84%
it's not really set, because
an agreement can always change.

00:23:48.210 --> 00:23:51.700 align:middle line:84%
Well like we see in this
picture, with your dad,

00:23:51.700 --> 00:23:54.400 align:middle line:84%
with your son,
and he's-- are you

00:23:54.400 --> 00:23:57.631 align:middle line:84%
imparting knowledge unto
your-- to your grandson

00:23:57.631 --> 00:23:58.330 align:middle line:90%
in this picture?

00:23:58.330 --> 00:24:00.776 align:middle line:84%
Is that what you're talking
about, is that intangible

00:24:00.776 --> 00:24:01.480 align:middle line:90%
knowledge?

00:24:01.480 --> 00:24:05.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, I am loving
him unconditionally.

00:24:05.940 --> 00:24:12.410 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's like a-- if you
want to learn any language,

00:24:12.410 --> 00:24:17.070 align:middle line:84%
you take this object, you
don't know how to say it,

00:24:17.070 --> 00:24:23.320 align:middle line:90%
and someone come and say vaso.

00:24:23.320 --> 00:24:27.210 align:middle line:90%


00:24:27.210 --> 00:24:28.689 align:middle line:84%
-Vaso.
-Vaso.

00:24:28.689 --> 00:24:30.180 align:middle line:90%
Now it's an agreement.

00:24:30.180 --> 00:24:31.410 align:middle line:90%
That is now vaso.

00:24:31.410 --> 00:24:32.880 align:middle line:90%
Now it's vaso.

00:24:32.880 --> 00:24:35.160 align:middle line:90%
in English, it's glass.

00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:36.400 align:middle line:90%
In Spanish, it's vaso.

00:24:36.400 --> 00:24:38.190 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:24:38.190 --> 00:24:41.240 align:middle line:84%
Now if you get it right,
you get the reward.

00:24:41.240 --> 00:24:43.260 align:middle line:90%
Yay. [CLAPPING]

00:24:43.260 --> 00:24:45.300 align:middle line:90%
And if you get to wrong, oh no.

00:24:45.300 --> 00:24:46.640 align:middle line:90%
Try again.

00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:50.750 align:middle line:90%
It's, see my lips, vaso.

00:24:50.750 --> 00:24:52.802 align:middle line:90%
Vaso.

00:24:52.802 --> 00:24:53.870 align:middle line:90%
Vaso.

00:24:53.870 --> 00:24:56.350 align:middle line:90%
Yay. [CLAPPING]

00:24:56.350 --> 00:25:01.610 align:middle line:84%
Every single part of
knowledge is an agreement.

00:25:01.610 --> 00:25:04.850 align:middle line:84%
It's still difficult to
learn a new language.

00:25:04.850 --> 00:25:08.380 align:middle line:84%
Then when you see a child
try to learn a language,

00:25:08.380 --> 00:25:10.890 align:middle line:84%
you'll see them make
a lot of mistakes.

00:25:10.890 --> 00:25:12.460 align:middle line:90%
It is so funny to see them--

00:25:12.460 --> 00:25:14.200 align:middle line:84%
But it's so beautiful,
because that's

00:25:14.200 --> 00:25:16.110 align:middle line:90%
how they relate to the world.

00:25:16.110 --> 00:25:19.320 align:middle line:84%
Things have labels and
words attached to them,

00:25:19.320 --> 00:25:22.630 align:middle line:84%
whereas they didn't have
that 2,500 years ago.

00:25:22.630 --> 00:25:25.640 align:middle line:84%
Then they know that
this is a glass.

00:25:25.640 --> 00:25:28.220 align:middle line:90%
It is part of his knowledge.

00:25:28.220 --> 00:25:30.670 align:middle line:84%
Which is when my father
says, domesticate him,

00:25:30.670 --> 00:25:32.560 align:middle line:84%
this is exactly what
he's talking about.

00:25:32.560 --> 00:25:35.940 align:middle line:84%
Educate your child
and let them see it.

00:25:35.940 --> 00:25:38.320 align:middle line:90%
Now the question is, how?

00:25:38.320 --> 00:25:41.190 align:middle line:84%
Because, as simple
as that was, there

00:25:41.190 --> 00:25:43.620 align:middle line:90%
sometimes goes to the extremes.

00:25:43.620 --> 00:25:46.740 align:middle line:84%
With every punishment,
oh, you're-- you can

00:25:46.740 --> 00:25:48.950 align:middle line:90%
see I could be very abusive.

00:25:48.950 --> 00:25:50.870 align:middle line:84%
I can punish him
with so much thing,

00:25:50.870 --> 00:25:53.870 align:middle line:84%
and I can fill him
with guilt, with shame,

00:25:53.870 --> 00:25:55.980 align:middle line:90%
with all these self-doubts.

00:25:55.980 --> 00:25:58.310 align:middle line:84%
And this is how we
acquire our knowledge.

00:25:58.310 --> 00:26:00.050 align:middle line:90%
The question is, how?

00:26:00.050 --> 00:26:04.720 align:middle line:84%
And an attachment, if you
can see how our knowledge is

00:26:04.720 --> 00:26:06.580 align:middle line:84%
completely subjugate
to an agreement

00:26:06.580 --> 00:26:09.310 align:middle line:84%
and can change at
any given moment,

00:26:09.310 --> 00:26:12.470 align:middle line:84%
an attachment is when we bring
something that's foreign,

00:26:12.470 --> 00:26:14.000 align:middle line:90%
and we make it part of us.

00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:16.840 align:middle line:90%
We bring it in.

00:26:16.840 --> 00:26:19.560 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things that
happens when we get attached

00:26:19.560 --> 00:26:22.200 align:middle line:90%
is, we don't want it to change.

00:26:22.200 --> 00:26:24.860 align:middle line:84%
Because if it changes,
what does it say about me?

00:26:24.860 --> 00:26:29.250 align:middle line:84%
So we attach ourselves to our
knowledge, and when we do that,

00:26:29.250 --> 00:26:32.630 align:middle line:84%
one of the worst things that
can happen is for it to change.

00:26:32.630 --> 00:26:36.270 align:middle line:84%
Because if it's wrong, what
does that say about me?

00:26:36.270 --> 00:26:39.950 align:middle line:84%
If it's right, well then I'm
better than everyone else.

00:26:39.950 --> 00:26:42.410 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
that's the war

00:26:42.410 --> 00:26:45.020 align:middle line:90%
that we have in our society.

00:26:45.020 --> 00:26:46.910 align:middle line:90%
Who can domesticate who?

00:26:46.910 --> 00:26:50.070 align:middle line:84%
Who can impose their
will on to someone,

00:26:50.070 --> 00:26:51.760 align:middle line:90%
and who's going to subjugate?

00:26:51.760 --> 00:26:54.710 align:middle line:84%
When you have two people trying
to impose onto each other,

00:26:54.710 --> 00:26:55.490 align:middle line:90%
we have conflict.

00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:58.630 align:middle line:84%
Who's going to domesticate
until someone gives in?

00:26:58.630 --> 00:27:01.920 align:middle line:84%
Well for the example of your
grandmother, your mother.

00:27:01.920 --> 00:27:04.850 align:middle line:84%
When she taught you
traditional ways-- and we

00:27:04.850 --> 00:27:09.700 align:middle line:84%
have a picture of her in a
wonderful, traditional outfit.

00:27:09.700 --> 00:27:13.390 align:middle line:84%
How do you take that
knowledge that she taught you,

00:27:13.390 --> 00:27:19.830 align:middle line:84%
and use that to guide you,
and also, at the same time,

00:27:19.830 --> 00:27:20.540 align:middle line:90%
let it go?

00:27:20.540 --> 00:27:22.120 align:middle line:90%
How do you detach from it?

00:27:22.120 --> 00:27:26.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, at the thing about it
is, one, the way my grandmother

00:27:26.010 --> 00:27:28.830 align:middle line:84%
taught-- this is the same
thing as my dad-- by action.

00:27:28.830 --> 00:27:30.960 align:middle line:84%
You can say, let's
use an example

00:27:30.960 --> 00:27:34.510 align:middle line:84%
that, when she began to teach
me was through translation.

00:27:34.510 --> 00:27:36.000 align:middle line:84%
I had to translate
for her because she

00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:37.440 align:middle line:90%
didn't speak any English.

00:27:37.440 --> 00:27:39.790 align:middle line:90%
So she only spoke Spanish.

00:27:39.790 --> 00:27:42.570 align:middle line:84%
So I had to speak for--
translate for her.

00:27:42.570 --> 00:27:44.420 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes she
would get inspired,

00:27:44.420 --> 00:27:47.922 align:middle line:84%
and she'd just go off, and
I have to try to catch up.

00:27:47.922 --> 00:27:50.350 align:middle line:84%
I was listening to
everything she was saying,

00:27:50.350 --> 00:27:52.690 align:middle line:84%
and I was processing
everything she

00:27:52.690 --> 00:27:53.890 align:middle line:84%
was saying, that
eventually I wasn't

00:27:53.890 --> 00:27:55.260 align:middle line:90%
listening to her anymore.

00:27:55.260 --> 00:27:58.790 align:middle line:84%
I was listening to my
own mind, processing it.

00:27:58.790 --> 00:28:01.070 align:middle line:84%
When my grandma
asked me, why do you

00:28:01.070 --> 00:28:02.650 align:middle line:84%
think you're having
so many problems

00:28:02.650 --> 00:28:04.350 align:middle line:90%
with translating my words?

00:28:04.350 --> 00:28:06.190 align:middle line:84%
I said, it's because
you're not giving

00:28:06.190 --> 00:28:08.730 align:middle line:90%
me a chance to translate.

00:28:08.730 --> 00:28:10.350 align:middle line:90%
You're going too fast.

00:28:10.350 --> 00:28:12.400 align:middle line:84%
And she said, are
you using knowledge,

00:28:12.400 --> 00:28:14.200 align:middle line:90%
or is knowledge using you?

00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:16.630 align:middle line:84%
Meaning by that, are you
listening to life, which

00:28:16.630 --> 00:28:18.860 align:middle line:84%
is my voice, or
are you listening

00:28:18.860 --> 00:28:22.360 align:middle line:84%
to your mind, which is
telling you how it should be.

00:28:22.360 --> 00:28:23.620 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're
paying attention

00:28:23.620 --> 00:28:25.520 align:middle line:84%
to your mind of
how it should be,

00:28:25.520 --> 00:28:27.540 align:middle line:84%
then you're no longer
listening to me.

00:28:27.540 --> 00:28:28.240 align:middle line:90%
That makes sense.

00:28:28.240 --> 00:28:29.260 align:middle line:90%
She's a very wise woman.

00:28:29.260 --> 00:28:29.960 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:28:29.960 --> 00:28:32.860 align:middle line:84%
She said, imagine
doing that to life.

00:28:32.860 --> 00:28:35.530 align:middle line:84%
You live life and you
process everything,

00:28:35.530 --> 00:28:39.000 align:middle line:84%
and you're completely
contemplating everything

00:28:39.000 --> 00:28:42.040 align:middle line:84%
so much that life
continues to move on,

00:28:42.040 --> 00:28:45.680 align:middle line:84%
and you've got behind on
something of what happened,

00:28:45.680 --> 00:28:48.300 align:middle line:84%
and you're trying
to understand it.

00:28:48.300 --> 00:28:50.160 align:middle line:84%
You're no longer
listening to life.

00:28:50.160 --> 00:28:53.530 align:middle line:84%
In fact, you're going to
impose what you know onto life,

00:28:53.530 --> 00:28:56.080 align:middle line:84%
and you're no longer
going to see it.

00:28:56.080 --> 00:28:59.310 align:middle line:90%
She told me, learn to listen.

00:28:59.310 --> 00:29:01.230 align:middle line:84%
Imagine that my voice
is the first thing

00:29:01.230 --> 00:29:04.510 align:middle line:84%
you hear in your mind,
and open your mouth,

00:29:04.510 --> 00:29:05.960 align:middle line:90%
and say it in English.

00:29:05.960 --> 00:29:07.900 align:middle line:84%
I was able to actually
get to the point

00:29:07.900 --> 00:29:11.590 align:middle line:84%
where, as she began to use the
first letters of each word,

00:29:11.590 --> 00:29:13.790 align:middle line:90%
I was already translating it.

00:29:13.790 --> 00:29:16.260 align:middle line:84%
She is such a wise woman,
and this picture is such

00:29:16.260 --> 00:29:17.370 align:middle line:90%
a wonderful picture of her.

00:29:17.370 --> 00:29:20.370 align:middle line:84%
And this is the way she
taught me how to meditate,

00:29:20.370 --> 00:29:24.300 align:middle line:84%
how to quiet the mind, how to
quiet everything around me.

00:29:24.300 --> 00:29:27.520 align:middle line:84%
Because I had to completely
shut everything around me

00:29:27.520 --> 00:29:28.880 align:middle line:90%
and listen.

00:29:28.880 --> 00:29:32.020 align:middle line:84%
This was her way of
teaching me how to meditate.

00:29:32.020 --> 00:29:35.650 align:middle line:84%
Something that, as I was a
young, I didn't understand.

00:29:35.650 --> 00:29:39.700 align:middle line:84%
But in that moment of transition
in my life, all of a sudden

00:29:39.700 --> 00:29:42.420 align:middle line:84%
it dawned on me, that
that's what I'm doing.

00:29:42.420 --> 00:29:44.450 align:middle line:90%
I'm projecting onto the world.

00:29:44.450 --> 00:29:48.100 align:middle line:84%
I have my own narrators
in my own mind, the voice

00:29:48.100 --> 00:29:50.910 align:middle line:84%
of my knowledge, in the
form of my thoughts,

00:29:50.910 --> 00:29:54.720 align:middle line:84%
describing everything of
how the world should be.

00:29:54.720 --> 00:29:57.330 align:middle line:90%
And life is what it is.

00:29:57.330 --> 00:30:01.940 align:middle line:84%
And when I'm fighting the world,
as this is how it should be,

00:30:01.940 --> 00:30:03.960 align:middle line:84%
then I'm going in complete
disharmony with the world,

00:30:03.960 --> 00:30:05.970 align:middle line:84%
because I'm not
paying attention.

00:30:05.970 --> 00:30:09.030 align:middle line:84%
Is-- is your life a
walking meditation?

00:30:09.030 --> 00:30:12.190 align:middle line:84%
Do you live in this
beautiful space of your heart

00:30:12.190 --> 00:30:13.310 align:middle line:90%
all the time?

00:30:13.310 --> 00:30:17.701 align:middle line:84%
Or do you have moments to take
you out of that, Don Miguel?

00:30:17.701 --> 00:30:20.670 align:middle line:90%
Well, it's very rare for sure.

00:30:20.670 --> 00:30:23.090 align:middle line:90%
Is it?

00:30:23.090 --> 00:30:24.819 align:middle line:84%
Mikey?
-For him?

00:30:24.819 --> 00:30:25.800 align:middle line:90%
Is it rare?

00:30:25.800 --> 00:30:27.100 align:middle line:90%
That he has--

00:30:27.100 --> 00:30:30.280 align:middle line:84%
Moments that takes him-- takes
him out of his heart space?

00:30:30.280 --> 00:30:33.610 align:middle line:84%
I would say, there are
moments where, when he's tired

00:30:33.610 --> 00:30:38.070 align:middle line:84%
and he's sleepy, when his
awareness is kind of a weak,

00:30:38.070 --> 00:30:41.040 align:middle line:84%
that sometimes, you know
like any-- any person who

00:30:41.040 --> 00:30:42.240 align:middle line:90%
gets tired, gets cranky.

