two books in particular.

00:45:20.100 --> 00:45:23.680 align:middle line:84%
A book called-- by Mary Carroll
Nelson called, "Beyond Fear",

00:45:23.680 --> 00:45:25.550 align:middle line:90%
and "The Four Agreements."

00:45:25.550 --> 00:45:29.560 align:middle line:84%
In "Beyond Fear", he talks
a lot about the Teotihuacan

00:45:29.560 --> 00:45:30.700 align:middle line:90%
Tezcatlipoca plain.

00:45:30.700 --> 00:45:33.740 align:middle line:84%
He talked a lot about
that old Shaman tradition.

00:45:33.740 --> 00:45:35.420 align:middle line:84%
But my father found
that a lot of people

00:45:35.420 --> 00:45:38.790 align:middle line:84%
were becoming fanatical
about that kind of teaching,

00:45:38.790 --> 00:45:41.900 align:middle line:90%
so he shifted the teaching.

00:45:41.900 --> 00:45:45.040 align:middle line:84%
He let's go of a lot
of that symbology,

00:45:45.040 --> 00:45:47.790 align:middle line:84%
and just stripped it
down to a language

00:45:47.790 --> 00:45:50.990 align:middle line:84%
that's common sense, at least
to my father's point of view.

00:45:50.990 --> 00:45:53.030 align:middle line:84%
And The Four
Agreements were born.

00:45:53.030 --> 00:45:55.650 align:middle line:84%
And you can say
that each generation

00:45:55.650 --> 00:45:57.380 align:middle line:90%
shares it in his own way.

00:45:57.380 --> 00:46:00.820 align:middle line:84%
If Don Ezekiel was
around and teaching us,

00:46:00.820 --> 00:46:05.090 align:middle line:84%
he was say-- he would speak to
